</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR167:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR167"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              167-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 167</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 110</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to world agritourism day. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 18, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 167, Hadwick.
                          World Agritourism Day.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would proclaim May 16, 2026, as World Agritourism Day.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_5AD9E449-0C40-413E-AAB6-BEC46FCF22C0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California is the nation’s leading agricultural state, producing more than 400 commodities and annually contributing tens of billions of dollars to the state’s economy; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_702CF124-DAD0-4C0D-9B2A-5E62426F53B7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Family farmers and ranchers across California steward millions of acres of working lands that provide food, fiber, wildlife habitat, and open space for future generations; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D7545998-7A08-4039-AB63-85C2F5ABD616"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Agritourism, activities that invite the public onto farms, ranches, and agricultural operations for educational, recreational, and cultural experiences, strengthen the connection between consumers and the agricultural producers who grow their food; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_22EE804B-6167-4BF2-A713-2D4DED6C36B3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Agritourism activities, such as farm tours, harvest festivals, farm stays, pumpkin patches, u-pick operations, farmers’ markets, and agricultural education programs, help Californians better understand where their food comes from and the hard work required to produce it; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_95B8ADEA-845B-4BF4-8FF3-A65C390A9290"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, These activities also provide farmers and ranchers with opportunities to diversify their income, helping sustain family farms and rural economies in the face of rising costs, drought, regulatory burdens, and market volatility; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FC802EDD-D4A5-4DF4-982C-29134C1AAF38"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Rural communities throughout California benefit from agritourism through increased visitation, local spending, and support for small businesses; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FE077C28-D49C-4B97-B267-A84202B76117"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Agritourism plays an important role in educating young people about agriculture, natural resources, conservation, and the importance of preserving California’s agricultural heritage; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CB825824-7085-4152-9303-7FD5FBF59EC1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, World Agritourism Day is celebrated internationally to highlight the value of agritourism in supporting farmers, strengthening rural communities, and promoting sustainable agricultural practices; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_D90536D7-899C-49D4-B364-98C78C48949E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature recognizes May 16, 2026, as World Agritourism Day and encourages all Californians to visit local farms and ranches, support agricultural producers, and learn more about the vital role agriculture plays in our state; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_B9CCA857-F7EE-425F-AC6C-9028ECDE4A10"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
